  concurrently learn about quantum mechanics and spherical harmonics from scratch, learn Qt from scratch, re-learn OpenGL and then  
  learn Vulkan from scratch, learn vcpkg from scratch, learn multi-OS deployment from scratch, and learn about lambdas and modern   
  threading from scratch. It was a very deep and wide forcing function to get my hands dirty and challenge myself. I'm sure there   
  are things I could or should have done better, but as a learning platform, what's your take on my approaches?                     
                                                                                                                                    
